    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Streaming Controls Guide",
      "gridPos": { "h": 7, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "id": 200,
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## ClickHouse Streaming Plugin Controls\n\nEnable **Streaming** toggle in the query editor to activate real-time data polling. The following controls appear:\n\n| Control | Description |\n|---|---|\n| **Streaming mode** | **Delta** — first poll fetches full range, subsequent polls fetch only new data. Efficient for heavy queries. Requires a time macro (`$timeFilter`, `$timeSeries`, etc.). **Full refresh** — re-runs the entire query each poll. Best for lightweight queries. Data is only sent to the panel when results change. |\n| **Poll interval** | How often ClickHouse is queried: `1s`, `2s`, `5s` (default), `10s`, `30s`, `1m`. Lower = fresher data, higher = less DB load. |\n| **Lookback points** | *(Delta mode only)* Number of recent data points to re-query each tick. Fixes incomplete GROUP BY buckets that are still receiving data. Default: `1`. Set higher (`3`–`5`) for coarse time buckets. |\n\n**Multi-series support:** Queries with `GROUP BY host` (or similar) produce multiple series on a single panel — handled automatically via wide-frame merge.\n\n**Panels below** demonstrate different combinations of mode, poll interval, and lookback. The bottom row shows non-streaming panels for comparison."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Delta mode",
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 7 },
      "id": 100,

      "collapsed": false
